WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.190 --> 00:00:04.049
Bolt-On is a Song of Ice and Fire fan theory that claims that Roose Bolton is a long-

00:00:04.049 --> 00:00:07.210
lived being of some kind who periodically steals other peoples' identities by

00:00:07.210 --> 00:00:08.880
removing and magically wearing their skin.

00:00:08.880 --> 00:00:13.349
What? Yes. Let's get into it. So what do we know about Roose Bolton?

00:00:13.349 --> 00:00:17.000
He's the Lord of the Dreadfort, head of the old and powerful House Bolton, and now Warden

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:19.020
of the North, after betraying the Starks.

00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:22.470
He's the father of Ramsay Bolton, and used to have another, trueborn, son,

00:00:22.470 --> 00:00:26.430
Domeric, who according to Roose was an all-round top bloke until Ramsay killed his half-

00:00:26.430 --> 00:00:27.410
brother with poison.

00:00:27.410 --> 00:00:32.059
Allegedly. We know that Roose is manipulative, cold, ambitious, and

00:00:32.059 --> 00:00:35.110
utterly ruthless. We know he has an enthusiasm for flaying,

00:00:35.110 --> 00:00:39.930
and leeches, and is generally a seriously creepy dude. But is he an ancient, skin-

00:00:39.930 --> 00:00:40.870
stealing monster?

00:00:40.870 --> 00:00:44.550
The natural first reaction to this theory is to dismiss it as crazy.

00:00:44.550 --> 00:00:48.270
And it is crazy. But is it more crazy than dragons, hundred-year-old psychic tree-

00:00:48.270 --> 00:00:52.610
people, ice zombies and stone zombies, mind-controlled giant wolves, necromancy, ten-

00:00:52.610 --> 00:00:53.370
year winters,

00:00:53.370 --> 00:00:57.010
a magic horn that roasts your innards, accurate prophecies, resurrection, magical

00:00:57.010 --> 00:00:58.410
disguises, Faceless Men,

00:00:58.410 --> 00:01:01.570
mammoth-riding giants attacking a 700 foot tall wall made of ice,

00:01:01.570 --> 00:01:05.040
and, if the show is to be believed, fireball-throwing skeleton-monster-fighting elf-

00:01:05.040 --> 00:01:05.630
children?

00:01:05.630 --> 00:01:09.820
Probably not. In fact, the Faceless Men of Braavos  definitively show that it

00:01:09.820 --> 00:01:12.990
is possible to magically wear someone else's skin as an effective disguise

00:01:12.990 --> 00:01:13.890
of the whole body.

00:01:13.890 --> 00:01:17.340
The Men literally remove the skin of peoples' faces and wear them in a magical

00:01:17.340 --> 00:01:19.340
process that involves cutting their own face,

00:01:19.340 --> 00:01:23.119
resulting in an disguise that we've seen to be wholly convincing. It seems to be a form of

00:01:23.119 --> 00:01:26.060
blood magic, which we've seen on a number of times to be very

00:01:26.060 --> 00:01:29.570
real magic. So we know that something like this is possible. And if it's 

00:01:29.570 --> 00:01:30.140
possible,

00:01:30.140 --> 00:01:33.570
you'd think the Boltons would know about it - they've been flaying people for centuries,

00:01:33.570 --> 00:01:37.040
so you'd think if anyone would discover this magic of blood and skin, they would.

00:01:37.040 --> 00:01:39.600
Hells, they could have gotten on a boat and found out from the Faceless Men

00:01:39.600 --> 00:01:41.030
themselves, like Arya does -

00:01:41.030 --> 00:01:44.409
they're practically neighbours with Braavos. In any case, it seems totally plausible

00:01:44.409 --> 00:01:47.619
that some kind of blood magic could be used by the Boltons to create

00:01:47.619 --> 00:01:51.040
convincing disguises from the skins of their flayed enemies. Which, by the way, they

00:01:51.040 --> 00:01:52.320
already wear as cloaks.

00:01:52.320 --> 00:01:55.340
Roose Bolton - or the creature wearing Roose Bolton's skin who for the sake of

00:01:55.340 --> 00:01:56.630
convenience we'll call Roose -

00:01:56.630 --> 00:02:00.229
could be doing this. What about the other part - could Roose have been hopping between

00:02:00.229 --> 00:02:01.890
identities over centuries?

00:02:01.890 --> 00:02:05.829
Could he be immortal? Well we certainly do have examples of immortal or at least

00:02:05.829 --> 00:02:07.540
very long-lived creatures.

00:02:07.540 --> 00:02:10.970
In fact, one of these possibilities is particularly relevant.

00:02:10.970 --> 00:02:15.560
Roose Bolton is described as pale and cold and almost all of his appearances in the

00:02:15.560 --> 00:02:16.890
books mention his strange

00:02:16.890 --> 00:02:20.599
pale eyes. Roose Bolton resembles an Other.

00:02:20.599 --> 00:02:23.750
But how could Roose Bolton be white walker, or something like one?

00:02:23.750 --> 00:02:28.099
Well, a possible explanation can be found in one of Old Nan's stories.

00:02:28.099 --> 00:02:31.360
Now while we are yet to see snarks or grumkins, a lot of what

00:02:31.360 --> 00:02:34.670
Old Nan says has been pretty accurate, like this stuff about wildlings.

00:02:34.670 --> 00:02:37.900
And remember that the Others themselves were supposedly just a story.

00:02:37.900 --> 00:02:41.910
More and more of the supernatural and mythical is turning out to be real, so it

00:02:41.910 --> 00:02:43.950
seems reasonable that we can learn from Old Nan's stories.

00:02:43.950 --> 00:02:47.950
Anyway the story goes that there once was a man who loved a woman with "skin as white as the

00:02:47.950 --> 00:02:49.970
moon and eyes like blue stars".

00:02:49.970 --> 00:02:53.200
She's pretty clearly an Other or something of the sort, and the man,

00:02:53.200 --> 00:02:55.099
who Nan says may have been a Bolton,

00:02:55.099 --> 00:02:59.349
"gave his seed ... [and his] soul" to the woman. Perhaps a child was born of this union.

00:02:59.349 --> 00:03:02.650
And given the importance of blood in A Song of Ice and Fire and its granting of

00:03:02.650 --> 00:03:03.569
certain powers,

00:03:03.569 --> 00:03:06.690
the child of a man and an Other might have
a longer life. Might

00:03:06.690 --> 00:03:11.420
have blue or otherwise strange eyes. He might just generally seem really creepy.

00:03:11.420 --> 00:03:14.680
Roose Bolton may be some kind of half-human

00:03:14.680 --> 00:03:18.269
half-Other - if not the Night's King himself - wearing human skin.

00:03:18.269 --> 00:03:21.650
So we have a possible explantion for the skin-stealing, and a possible

00:03:21.650 --> 00:03:24.370
explanation for the longevity and eyes and creepiness.

00:03:24.370 --> 00:03:28.080
This really does seems possible. But is there any direct evidence?

00:03:28.080 --> 00:03:31.099
Not really. There is this passage -

00:03:31.099 --> 00:03:35.040
"Roose Bolton’s ... face [is] a pale grey mask, with two chips of dirty ice

00:03:35.040 --> 00:03:38.340
where his eyes should be". That fits perfectly with the theory, right?

00:03:38.340 --> 00:03:42.470
His skin is a mask, his eyes are ice - but it could be no more than poetic language

00:03:42.470 --> 00:03:45.790
to say that his face and eyes are emotionless and give nothing away

00:03:45.790 --> 00:03:49.200
and are harsh. But there is more stuff that makes a lot of sense with this theory.

00:03:49.200 --> 00:03:52.840
Did you ever wonder why Roose puts up with, let alone legitimises, the psychotic and

00:03:52.840 --> 00:03:54.030
unpredictable Ramsay?

00:03:54.030 --> 00:03:57.000
Roose implies that the only reason he doesn't kill Ramsay for murdering Domeric

00:03:57.000 --> 00:03:58.620
was because that would be kinslaying.

00:03:58.620 --> 00:04:02.620
Does the man who breaks guest right to betray and slaughter his allies really care

00:04:02.620 --> 00:04:03.689
about kinslaying?

00:04:03.689 --> 00:04:07.040
And if he needs an heir, couldn't he and Walda just have a child who's,

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:11.830
y'know, less bad for PR? This theory gives Roose a reason to keep Ramsay around.

00:04:11.830 --> 00:04:14.970
Roose plans to take Ramsay's skin and identity.

00:04:14.970 --> 00:04:19.019
I mean he'd need to change bodies eventually, right, so people don't get suspicious as Roose enters

00:04:19.019 --> 00:04:20.579
his 50s and 60s and onwards

00:04:20.579 --> 00:04:23.830
without visibly aging. Ramsay is a perfect candidate -

00:04:23.830 --> 00:04:27.410
once legitimised, Ramsay becomes the heir of the Dreadfort and the North,

00:04:27.410 --> 00:04:30.160
and further, his eyes are said to look like Roose's.

00:04:30.160 --> 00:04:33.380
This is important, because if Ramsay's eyes suddenly changed to Roose's

00:04:33.380 --> 00:04:34.470
distinctive wight-like

00:04:34.470 --> 00:04:38.810
eyes, people could get suspicious. And we know from this passage that they must be

00:04:38.810 --> 00:04:40.490
very distinctive.

00:04:40.490 --> 00:04:43.660
Another possible meaning is that the Other-like eyes indicate that Ramsay, like

00:04:43.660 --> 00:04:44.139
Roose,

00:04:44.139 --> 00:04:47.400
has some degree of Other-ness, and Roose wants to keep him around for that

00:04:47.400 --> 00:04:48.500
reason.

00:04:48.500 --> 00:04:51.810
Either way, if Roose has an interest in pale-eyed Ramsay being his heir,

00:04:51.810 --> 00:04:56.389
maybe Roose killed Domeric. I mean, poison hardly seems to be Ramsay's style, right?

00:04:56.389 --> 00:05:00.430
Maybe this bastard is innocent after all. Maybe Roose killed these other children as

00:05:00.430 --> 00:05:00.870
well for

00:05:00.870 --> 00:05:05.330
lacking his strange pale eyes. 
Another thing that this theory explains is Roose's

00:05:05.330 --> 00:05:06.570
use of leeches.

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:10.039
We know from Coldhands that "once the heart has ceased to beat, a man’s blood runs

00:05:10.039 --> 00:05:11.300
down into his extremities,

00:05:11.300 --> 00:05:14.880
where it thickens and congeals”, causing “his hands and feet swell up

00:05:14.880 --> 00:05:18.560
and turn as black as pudding". Roose says that "frequent leechings are the secret of

00:05:18.560 --> 00:05:19.240
a long life.

00:05:19.240 --> 00:05:22.470
A man must purge himself of bad blood". He could be leeching

00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:25.490
to prevent this conspicuous condition from setting in.

00:05:25.490 --> 00:05:29.210
Alright so we've got an idea of the theory, let's quickly look at an objection to it.

00:05:29.210 --> 00:05:32.139
It could be argued that it's a bit inconsistent for Roose Bolton to be a

00:05:32.139 --> 00:05:33.560
supernatural evil monster

00:05:33.560 --> 00:05:38.030
rather than a human monster. A Song of Ice and Fire explores the nature and reality of

00:05:38.030 --> 00:05:39.210
human evil.

00:05:39.210 --> 00:05:43.270
It's not about good guys fighting evil monsters, it's about complex human beings

00:05:43.270 --> 00:05:47.220
who do wrong for love and to belong and to deal with their brokenness and as a

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:48.610
result a harsh world,

00:05:48.610 --> 00:05:52.900
as well as for plain psychotic madness. Isn't that cheapened by having evil

00:05:52.900 --> 00:05:54.419
explained by making someone

00:05:54.419 --> 00:05:57.560
an inhuman monster? One problem with this argument is that

00:05:57.560 --> 00:06:01.180
we already have the Others, right? There are supernatural, seemingly

00:06:01.180 --> 00:06:05.880
evil monsters in A Song of Ice and Fire. Roose is just another Other right?

00:06:05.880 --> 00:06:09.720
And perhaps not even than much of an evil one. Roose is cruel to his people,

00:06:09.720 --> 00:06:12.740
but that maintains "a peaceful land, a quiet people" -

00:06:12.740 --> 00:06:16.509
it works. And as for the Red Wedding, that ends a war that otherwise would have

00:06:16.509 --> 00:06:21.080
caused far more death and destruction and misery than ever occurs at the Twins.

00:06:21.080 --> 00:06:24.300
We've never had a point of view chapter with Roose, or meta-Other-Roose,

00:06:24.300 --> 00:06:26.000
so we haven't had a chance to see things from

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:29.020
his or its point of view. Perhaps this monster

00:06:29.020 --> 00:06:32.979
is more human than some of the humans
we've seen in the Song after all.

00:06:32.979 --> 00:06:36.069
The point is that things may be more complicated than they seem, and so it's

00:06:36.069 --> 00:06:38.960
probably too early to declare this theory inconsistent with the themes of

00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:43.259
A Song of Ice and Fire, and even if it is who gives a grumkin's arse, it's cool.

00:06:43.259 --> 00:06:48.520
Um. Let's end there. Bolt-On does seem plausible, but there isn't any hugely

00:06:48.520 --> 00:06:51.669
compelling evidence either way so all these vague hints could well amount

00:06:51.669 --> 00:06:52.930
to nothing more than a red -

00:06:52.930 --> 00:06:56.479
or creepily pale - herring. Either way it's fun to think about.

00:06:56.479 --> 00:06:59.050
So thanks for watching this video, let me know what you want to see next.

